Pelvic endometriosis with urologic involvement. Therapeutic principles: apropos of 2 cases. The authors report 2 clinical cases of vesicopelvic endometriosis. The urinary symptoms and the radiological appearance of endometriosis of the bladder are nonspecific. The diagnosis was established by histological examination of the resection specimen. The authors describe the therapeutic approach based on radical surgery designed to eradicate the endometriosis, while remaining as conservative as possible in order to allow subsequent pregnancy, and the place of urological surgery combined with medical treatment with LHRH analogue.